en: َThe McGill Arabic Calligraphy Collection is a collection of manuscripts and printed books that feature Persian and  Arabic calligraphy. The collection includes works from the 16th to the 19th centuries, and it features a variety of styles of calligraphy, including Naskh, Thuluth, and Diwani. The collection is housed at McGill University in Montreal, Canada.
